<item>
            <title>[LU-4682] Accessing migrating directory get IO error.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4682</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;John identify some problems for this patch.&lt;br/&gt;
1. create a 4 MDTs FS. 2. on the client side, one terminal will do this&lt;br/&gt;
mkdir /mnt/lustre/test1 touch /mnt/lustre/test1/a MDTCOUNT=4&lt;br/&gt;
while true; do&lt;br/&gt;
        mdt_idx=$((RANDOM % MDTCOUNT))&lt;br/&gt;
        ../utils/lfs mv -M $mdt_idx /mnt/lustre/test1 &lt;br/&gt;
done&lt;br/&gt;
3. another terminal will do&lt;br/&gt;
ls /mnt/lustre/test1 cp /etc/fstab /mnt/lustre/test1&lt;br/&gt;
and we can see some IO error during the process.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will fix this problem in a later patch.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
